{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in rhubarb and 50 g sugar. Remove, mix together then set aside.","Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease sides and line base of a spring form tin (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper.","Place almonds and orange peel in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add eggs, baking powder, remaining 150 g sugar, butter, flour and orange juice then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix again <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add reserved rhubarb and sugar then fold in gently with spatula. Transfer to prepared tin and sprinkle with flaked almonds. Bake for 50-60 minutes (180°C) until golden brown and cooked through. Cool in tin for 20 minutes before removing to a wire rack.","Serve warm or cold, cut in slices, with cream."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g rhubarb, cut in pieces (2 cm)","200 g golden caster sugar","150 g unsalted butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","120 g almonds","1 orange, thin peelings of skin and 50 g juice","2 large eggs","½ tsp baking powder","100 g self-raising flour","25 g flaked almonds"]}],"id":"r94321","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-rIcuMdN759c\/XZWrdGXXkwI\/AAAAAAAAfno\/8VvTUJhW1a0e9_2ZILnVKU6iUeoaAz3mwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lvAOrbIPJ4KzkfbI.png","title":"Rhubarb, Orange and Almond Cake","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.3 g","fat":"27.3 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"38.6 g","calories":"1795 kJ \/ 429 kcal"},"usefulItems":"spring form tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, wire rack, oven","basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 30m","8 slices"]}